Package: input-remapper
Version: 2.2.0
Architecture: all
Section: utils
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Sezanzeb <b8x45ygc9@mozmail.com>
Homepage: https://github.com/gypg7p6c24-byte/input-remapper
Depends: python3, python3-evdev, python3-dasbus, python3-gi, python3-cairo, python3-pydantic, python3-packaging, python3-psutil, pkexec, polkitd, libgtk-3-0, gir1.2-gtk-3.0, gir1.2-gtksource-4
Recommends: gir1.2-appindicator3-0.1
Description: Remap Linux input devices, shortcuts, and macros
 Input Remapper provides a GTK interface to remap keyboards, mice,
 gamepads, and keypads on Linux. It supports autoloaded per-game presets,
 macros, and device-specific remapping through evdev/uinput.
Replaces: python3-key-mapper, key-mapper, input-remapper-gtk, input-remapper-daemon, python3-inputremapper
Conflicts: python3-key-mapper, key-mapper, input-remapper-gtk, input-remapper-daemon, python3-inputremapper
